quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,82,""
  26,83,"My Lord! Bestow Hukm (religious knowledge, right judgement of the affairs and Prophethood) on me, and join me with the righteous."
  26,84,"And grant me an honourable mention in later generations."
  27,55,""
  27,56,"There was no other answer given by his people except that they said: "
  27,57,"So We saved him and his family, except his wife. We destined her to be of those who remained behind."
  28,28,"He [Mûsâ (Moses)] said: "
  28,29,"Then, when Mûsâ (Moses) had fulfilled the term, and was travelling with his family, he saw a fire in the direction of Tûr (Mount). He said to his family: "
  28,30,"So when he reached it (the fire), he was called from the right side of the valley, in the blessed place, from the tree: "